components.description:
A friendly, cartoon-styled whale, shown spouting water from its blowhole. Generally depicted as a light-blue whale in full profile facing left, with a round body and white underside, its tail held upright.

Often used with an affectionate tone. Not to be confused with the more lifelike üêã Whale, though their applications may overlap.

WhatsApp’s whale is gray, as Microsoft and Facebook’s whales previously were. Twitter’s whale was previously purple.

version.description:
Released in October 2010, Unicode 6.0 was the first version of the Unicode Standard to support emoji.

Some characters in prior versions of Unicode were retroactively updated to provide an emoji presentation. This release was the first to introduce new characters for the sole purpose of compatability with emojis being used in Japan.

emoji_net_data.definition: A whale emoji, spouting water out of its blowhole. Shows with a more cartoon-like appearance on iOS, compared to the regular whale emoji. Sp http://emojipedia.org/spouting-whale/

bn:00089126v: To flow forth suddenly, in great volume.
To gush forth in a jet or stream
Gush forth in a sudden stream or jet
To cause to gush out suddenly or violently in a stream or jet.

bn:00069946n: The sea, the world ocean, or simply the ocean, is the connected body of salty water that covers 70.8% of the Earth's surface.
A large body of salty water. (Major seas are known as oceans.)
A sea is a large body of saline water usually connected with an ocean.
A division of an ocean or a large body of salt water partially enclosed by land
The body of water covering most of Earth
A body of salt water that is smaller than an ocean and generally in proximity to a continent.

bn:00058574n: The oceans, seas, bays, estuaries, and other major water bodies, including coastal marine and nearshore zones.
The mass of water occupying all of the Earth's surface not occupied by land, but excluding all lakes and inland seas.
Oceans are major bodies of saline water, and the principal component of the hydrosphere.
A large body of water constituting a principal part of the hydrosphere
An ocean is a body of saline water that composes much of a planet's hydrosphere.

bn:00080949n: Large marine mammals of the order Cetacea; the body is streamlined, the broad flat tail is used for propulsion, and the limbs are balancing structures.
Any of the larger cetacean mammals having a streamlined body and breathing through a blowhole on the head
Whale is the common name for various marine mammals of the order Cetacea.
Any of several species of large sea mammals of the order Cetacea.

apple_vendor_description: On Apple devices, the spouting whale is a magnificent sight, captured mid-breach with a powerful jet of water arcing gracefully from its blowhole. The whale itself boasts a smooth, dark gray skin with subtle highlights that emphasize its sleek, aquatic form, a hallmark of Apple's 3D rendering. This majestic emoji on Apple devices symbolizes the vastness of nature, power, and moments of joyful or surprising emergence, ideal for sharing awe-inspiring experiences or expressing a sense of grand scale.
